Harmony Pena – User Story 2

Actors:
•    Student: an individual that is a part of a group/team
•    Professor: the individual that provides all the assignment material & tasks

Name: Project Completion Status Check
Created by: Harmony Jackson (Pena)

Actors involved:
•	Triggered actor: Student
•	Secondary actor: Professor

Brief Description: The complete status of a project can be viewed in a separate area of the calendar/app
Triggering Event(s): As students mark assignments/tasks complete and the complete status of the project is updated

Priority: Medium
Preconditions: The Professor has provided all project assignments/tasks to the students
Assumptions: All project assignments/tasks have been uploaded to the calendar

The flow of events:
1.	Project assignments are uploaded by the Professor 
2.	The task manager assigns tasks to team members
3.	Completed assignments are marked done
4.	The complete status of the project is updated 
5.	Students click on “Project Name > Complete Status Check”

Alternative/Abnormal flow of events: 
1.	If the professor has not provided all assignments/tasks, the status of the project is invalid

Postconditions:
-	Students can view a live up-to-date status of the group’s project
---------------
User Stories:

1.	As a student, I want to be able to view an up-to-date status of my group’s project, so that I can know where the project stands.
2.	As a Professor, I want to be able to keep up with each team’s project progress, to ensure everyone is on the same page and understands the assignment/tasks.
